    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down. | Bromley. | Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Feb 22.</date>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I should be very much obliged if you w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> send me any printed document by which I c<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> learn something about the course of studies at King’s College for the sake of one of my sons.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>I wish for instance to know whether the students are allowed any choice in their particular lines of study, &amp; whether they are compelled to reside in the College.</p>
<p>I should therefore be much obliged if you c<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> send me any paper that w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> give me such information.</p>
<p>I beg leave to remain Sir | your obedient servant. | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">CD refers to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1230.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Leonard Darwin</ref>, who was 17 years old and attending Clapham Grammar School. No further correspondence with King’s College has been found. Ultimately, Leonard attended the Royal Military Academy, Woolwich.</note>
        </div>        
            
